{"id":14881779,"mediaExerciseId":"906bc995-23c9-4448-98e7-7f97a4d16b49","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612471,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":737,"solutions":[{"id":5990767,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the inflation rate in each situation using the international Fisher Effect.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **international Fisher effect** is a theory stating the real interest rates **are the same** between countries.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The formula of international Fisher effect is as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$R_{US}$}-\\text{$h_{US}$} &=\\text{$R_{FC}$}-\\text{$h_{FC}$}\\\\[10pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\\\n$R_{US}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of U.S.\n\n$R_{FC}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of a foreign country\n\n$h_{FC}$ = Inflation rate in a foreign country\n\n$h_{US}$ = Inflation rate in a U.S.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Since what we are looking for is the **inflation rate in a foreign country**, we need to derive the formula. Hence, the computation that will be used in the exercise is as follows:\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{$R_{FC}$}-\\text{$R_{US}$}+\\text{$h_{US}$}\\\\[10pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\n$R_{US}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of U.S. \n\n$R_{FC}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of a foreign country \n\n$h_{FC}$ = Inflation rate in a foreign country\n\n$h_{US}$ = Inflation rate in a U.S.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement A\n\nWe are asked to determine the inflation rate of Australia.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/56a26f86f5c8eb153aaba8c139b6af4f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/56a26f86f5c8eb153aaba8c139b6af4f/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following:\n<center>\n\n| | | \n|--|:--:| \n|$h_{US}$ | 3.5% | \n|$R_{US}$| 4.1% | \n|$R_{FC}$| 4% | \n\n</center>\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":63,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/1a974112af20aa5b66b20dc50ff3dd1e/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/1a974112af20aa5b66b20dc50ff3dd1e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Applying the formula in step 4:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{$R_{FC}$}-\\text{$R_{US}$}+\\text{$h_{US}$}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{0.04}-\\text{0.041}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{- 0.001}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\boxed{\\text{0.034}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n&nbsp;\nThe inflation rate in Australia is **3.4%**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":246,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/a023492f5d116c56c78a32f52d100e48/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":124,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/a023492f5d116c56c78a32f52d100e48/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement B\n\nWe are asked to determine the inflation rate of Canada.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":328,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/d77f284cbdf0621e1672deb1d45c054f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":165,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/d77f284cbdf0621e1672deb1d45c054f/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following:\n<center>\n\n| | | \n|--|:--:| \n|$h_{US}$ | 3.5% | \n|$R_{US}$| 4.1% | \n|$R_{FC}$| 7% | \n\n</center>\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"Applying the formula in step 4:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{$R_{FC}$}-\\text{$R_{US}$}+\\text{$h_{US}$}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{0.07}-\\text{0.041}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{0.029}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\boxed{\\text{0.064}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n&nbsp;\nThe inflation rate in Canada is **6.4%**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/b942c80411da015e831e71fd8f4a2505/lateximg_large.png","width":756},"regular":{"height":54,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/b942c80411da015e831e71fd8f4a2505/lateximg.png","width":378}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement C\n\nWe are asked to determine the inflation rate of Taiwan.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following:\n<center>\n\n| | | \n|--|:--:| \n|$h_{US}$ | 3.5% | \n|$R_{US}$| 4.1% | \n|$R_{FC}$| 9% | \n\n</center>\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":12},{"columns":[{"text":"Applying the formula in step 4:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{$R_{FC}$}-\\text{$R_{US}$}+\\text{$h_{US}$}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{0.09}-\\text{0.041}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\text{0.049}+\\text{0.035}\\\\\n\\text{$h_{FC}$} &=\\boxed{\\text{0.084}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n&nbsp;\nThe inflation rate in Taiwan is **8.4%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/8cc02dc84c8fee38ca5e810607d4b8ca/lateximg_large.png","width":756},"regular":{"height":54,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/334d888cdd8c57d038c14e5f136620b9/8cc02dc84c8fee38ca5e810607d4b8ca/lateximg.png","width":378}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":13},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the inflation rate in Australia, Canada, and Taiwan are **3.4%, 6.4%, and 8.4%** respectively.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":14}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"aec44e82-6cf4-4946-a305-a857d364bf66","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":14}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBe